@node main resend

                                @{b}resend, v2.00
                                -------------@{ub}

Resend will re-export messages directly without using TechMail. This
program is freeware and freely distributable. ©1996 by Sami Klemola.
All Rights Reserved.

         @{" Command specification                " link resend_1}
         @{" Contact addresses                    " link resend_2}

This program uses tech.lib and fidonet.lib, which are linker libraries
providing easy-use functions to access TechnoBBS related things and to
write fidonet mail packets. These are publically available for any
developer, and may be downloaded from the Aminet. Source code for the
program is available at request.
@endnode
@node resend_1 "Command specification"
@{b}Command specification@{ub}

                                  @{b}resend@{ub}

@{i}Format:@{ui}           resend <From> <To> <Date> <Origin> [NETMAIL]

@{i}Template:@{ui}         FROM/A/N,TO/A/N,DATE/A,ORIGIN/A,NETMAIL/S

@{i}Purpose:@{ui}          To re-export messages

@{i}Specification:@{ui}

Resend is a TechnoBBS utility, that will re-export messages directly
reading from your message base and writing to a fidonet packet. The
reason why I wrote this program, is that one of my network bosses
goofed up, and he lost all mail sent by my system for many weeks.
The only way to resend the lost messages using the TechnoBBS software
would have been to set back the hiwater marks and manually edit the
Sent flag of each message. This of course is a task too great to even
be concidered.

Resend does the job. It will scan each area (from From to To) and start
going through the messages starting at the first message entered on the
specified date or later. Messages that match Origin will be exported
into T:00000000.PKT. Specify the NETMAIL option if you want to make the
messages private. In other words, resend will write every message entered
at Origin after Date into the packet, which you would then send to your
boss.

@{i}Examples:@{ui}

    resend 2 2 10-Mar-96 65:10/5 NETMAIL

This will send all netmail messages (area 2) entered here on 10th March
or later. The messages will have the PRIVATE flag set in their attribute
word. Only messages going to the network in concern will be exported,
since others do not match the Origin having one of your other Origin
addresses.

    resend 21 55 22-Feb-96 65:10/5

This will send all messages from echo areas 21 through 55 entered on
February 22 or later.

Note! You may encounter hangups. Some systems send illegal messages,
and resend may not be able to correctly handle them.
@endnode
